// @test regression/INV016-union-arg-valid
// @description Union-arg validation (INV016) must accept in-set args and must NOT flag args whose type comes from an unreliable source (UDF returns, user vars) - that conservatism is what keeps it FP-free. nz(close)/math.max/int(close)/nz(<color>) are all in-set; the UDF-typed value is deliberately left unchecked.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects no-errors
//@version=6
indicator("INV016 union-arg valid")
myVal() => 0.0
v = myVal()
plot(nz(close))
plot(math.max(close, open))
x = int(close)
bgcolor(nz(close > open ? color.red : color.green))
plot(nz(v) + x)
